HEADWORD: Crown office
<hw>Crown" of`fice</hw> <pr>(?f`f?s; 115)</pr>. <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld>
<def>The criminal branch of the Court of King's or Queen's Bench,
commonly called the <xex>crown side</xex> of the court, which takes
cognizance of all criminal cases.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

